Architecture Doc: Authorised Capital Changes Pipeline
What I Built (The TL;DR)
At its core, this is an automated document intelligence pipeline powered by LangGraph. It chews through a folder of raw Indian MCA corporate filings (mostly Markdown), figures out what each file is, rips out the structured data, runs strict math and cross-reference checks, and finally spits out a clean, traceable capital history table in both JSON and HTML.

Why I Needed This
If you've ever dealt with Indian corporate filings, you know the pain. When a company updates its authorised capital (Form SH-7), they can't just submit the form—they have to drop a whole bundle of supporting documents, like Board Resolutions, EGM/AGM Resolutions, and MOA Clause V amendments.

Trying to manually reconcile all this paperwork across multiple historical events (say, tracking a company from 2018 to 2019, then 2021, and 2024) is a massive headache and super prone to human error. I built this system to completely automate that reconciliation. There is zero human-in-the-loop here. If something doesn't line up, the pipeline flags the discrepancy instead of taking wild guesses.


